data.name: Stuffed Portobello Mushrooms with Spinach and Cheese
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously stuffed mushrooms bursting with flavor and nutrients, paired with crispy Brussels sprouts.
detailedCookingInstructions: Clean the Portobello mushrooms and remove the stems; set aside.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat, add minced garlic, and sauté for 1-2 minutes until fragrant.
Add fresh spinach to the skillet and cook until wilted, about 3-4 minutes.
In a bowl, combine the cooked spinach, feta cheese, toasted pine nuts, grated Parmesan, salt, and pepper. Mix well.
Stuff each Portobello mushroom cap with the spinach and cheese mixture, pressing it down gently to pack it in.
Place the stuffed mushrooms on a baking sheet and bake for 25 minutes until the mushrooms are tender and the tops are golden.
While the mushrooms bake, prepare the Brussels sprouts by halving them and tossing them in olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast them in the oven for 20 minutes or until crispy and browned.
